This is the moment the world's only surviving set of giant panda triplets opened their eyes for the first time - more than a month after their birth.

The trio were hailed as a 'miracle' because of the animal's famously low reproductive rate.

Mother panda Ju Xiao, meaning 'chrysanthemum smile', delivered the triplets at Guangzhou's Chimelong Safari Park in the early hours of July 29.

